We move from counting entities and objects to identifying cardinality assertions. As defined in Section (ref), cardinality assertions specify the number of records in the ideal KB {{2305.05403_FO0092||FO}} that satisfy a certain property. But {{2305.05403_FO0093||FO}} is a hypothetically ideal KB, making the computation of cardinality assertions through selection conditions non-trivial.